Class DecodePostNet

java.lang.Object
DecodePostNet
public class DecodePostNet extends Object
DecodePostNet class provides methods for decoding a binary representation string into ZIP/ZIP+4/DIP+4+Delivery codes.

    • setBinaryRep

      public static void setBinaryRep(String binaryRep)
      The setter for setting the binaryRep. This method checks for a valid binaryRep entry. binaryRep must be 32, 52, or 62 digits long. If valid, binaryRep is set to provided value. If not valid, binaryRep is set as a default "11111111111111111111111111111111" value.
      Parameters:
      binaryRep - binary representation to set

    • getDigit

      public static int getDigit(String binaryDigits)
      Get the decimal value of binary digits. This method takes a chunk of binary digits 5 digits long and runs through the indexes of BINARY_NUMBERS. If the chunk matches with one of the indexes of BINARY_NUMBERS, its index is returned which will be its decimal value. This method is utilized within extractBinaryRepresentation method.
      Parameters:
      binaryDigits - The binary digits to convert.
      Returns:
      The index of where the chunk of binary digits was found within BINARY_NUMBERS. Or -1 if nothing is found.

    • decodeZipcode

      public static String decodeZipcode(String binaryRep)
      Decode a binary representation into a ZIP code. This method takes a binary representation as input and trims off the borders and the check sum. Uses the extractBinaryRepresentation method to decode into ZIP code.
      Parameters:
      binaryRep - The binary representation to be decoded.
      Returns:
      The decoded ZIP code as a string.

    • extractBinaryRepresentation

      private static String extractBinaryRepresentation(String binaryRep)
      Extract binary digits and decode into a numeric ZIP code representation. This method takes a binary representation string as input. Extracts binary digits in chunks of 5 with the use of substring. Uses the getDigit method to decode these chunks of binary digits. getDigit returns the index of where the chunk was found within BINARY_NUMBERS which happens to be the numeric value which is appended to the zipCode string. The finished zipCode string is returned. Uses StringBuilder to make the zipCode string.
      Parameters:
      binaryRep - The binary representation to extract and decode.
      Returns:
      The decoded ZIP code as a string.
